Residents of Umlazi township in the country have been sitting with piles of rubbish for over a week. eNCA’s Lethiwe Mdluli has the details. Courtesy #DStv403 DURBAN - Residents of Umlazi township have been sitting with piles of rubbish for over a week. The Umlazi community is demanding answers from the eThekwini Municipality. They are saying that their refuse is not being collected. READ: Umlazi community drowning in garbage waste But the municipality says its workers are being intimidated, forcing it to stop refuse collection. Residents now say the metro must outsource the service